The best-performing 2016 KCPE candidate scored 436 marks, 13 points lower that the highest score the previous year.Education CS Fred Matiang'i unexpectedly announced the results on Thursday, taking officials like Knut secretary general Wilson Sossion by surprise.Matiang'i reported that the top special needs student scored 421 marks."After the directive by the President, we registered the special needs candidates and they performed really well," he said.The number of special needs students who wrote the exam was 1,950.Some 5,190 candidates scored more than 400 marks compared to last year s 7,560 from a total list of 937,467 candidates.Matiang'i said 201,986 students attained marks between 301 and 400.Some 499,568 scored between 201 and 300, 215,614 from 101 to 200 marks and 3,061 less than 100 points.Matiang'i said form 1 selection will be finalised on December 9 and that students will report to school on January 9, 2017.Read: Sossion shocked as Matiang'i releases KCPE results todayAlso read: Top performers in 2015 KCPE examStudents who would like to know their results can send their index numbers to 22253.